  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance & Administration Executive",
  "description": "<p>The <strong>Landscape Industry Association (Singapore) – LIAS</strong> is looking for a meticulous and responsible <strong>Finance & Administration Executive</strong> to support our Secretariat team. The role involves managing financial accounts, handling daily operational finance matters, and providing administrative support for association activities. </p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage invoicing, payments, and financial record-keeping.</li><li>Handle <strong>GST submissions, tax matters, and payroll administration</strong> (including CPF).</li><li>Assist in <strong>budget tracking, audit preparation, and compliance reporting</strong>.</li><li>Support operational and administrative functions, including procurement, coordination of meetings, and documentation.</li><li><strong>Assist in event preparations</strong> and provide on-site support during <strong>workshops, seminars, and association events</strong>.</li><li>Work closely with the Secretariat team on association projects and initiatives.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in <strong>Accounting, Finance, or Business Administration</strong>.</li><li>At least <strong>2–3 years of relevant experience</strong>.</li><li>Proficient in <strong>accounting software</strong> (Xero/QuickBooks/MYOB) and MS Office.</li><li>Knowledge of Singapore’s accounting, GST, and payroll standards.</li><li>Singaporean or PR Resident</li><li>Able to work independently.</li><li>Strong organisational skills, attention to detail, and ability to manage multiple tasks.</li><li>A team player with a positive, responsible, and service-oriented attitude.</li><li>Prior experience working in an association, non-profit, or membership-based organisation will be an advantage.</li></ul><p><strong>Work Arrangement:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Hybrid work model:</strong> 2 days in office and 3 days remote work per week (subject to operational needs).</li></ul>",
